<ITEM>page 1</ITEM>
<LABEL>LETTER II. The Author expre&s;&s;es his a&s;toni&s;hment at his birth not having been pred$cted, and the neglect of the adepts in not calculating his nativity. Eulogy on taylors and &s;hoemakers. His genealogy and au&s;picious birth. Cen&s;ure of his father. Encomium on his mother.</LABEL>
<ITEM>page 6</ITEM>
<LABEL>LETTER III. Our hero is &s;ent to &s;chool. His wonderful progre&s;s in learning. A recapitulation of &s;ome of his juvenile exploits. Becomes agent to an eminent <HI>pie merchant.</HI> More ingenious exploits. Elopes. Is by his father initiated into the <HI>gentle craft.</HI></LABEL>
