<ITEM>page 55</ITEM>
<LABEL>LETTER IX. Farther particulars of methodi&s;m. Watch nights. Cla&s;&s;es. Bands. Select bands. Tickets.</LABEL>
<ITEM>page 61</ITEM>
<LABEL><PB N="xxiv" REF="23">LETTER X. The &s;ubject of methodi&s;m continued. Our hero &s;uddenly becomes a back&s;lider. An election for members of parliament. His freedom purcha&s;ed. Its con&s;e|quences to the author. Riot. Di&s;&s;ipation. Remor&s;e. An endeavour made to controul him. Revolts. Vi&s;its Wellington and Bri&s;tol. Returns to Taunton. Our hero enamoured. Accompanied by his <HI>fair one</HI> to Bridgewater, to Exbridge. Leaves her. Arrives at Bri&s;tol. Pur&s;ued by pari&s;h officers. E&s;capes. Story of a blundering o&s;tler and an <HI>amorous</HI> gentle|man.</LABEL>
